1
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:55,740
=Sugar and Lies=
(A Different Her: The Women's Trilogy)

2
00:00:56,820 --> 00:00:59,780
=Episode 8=
=We Can't Go Back=

3
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,140
You're acting so natural now.

4
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,080
You've changed.

5
00:01:13,720 --> 00:01:15,240
Then what was I like back then?

6
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:17,520
Who was the one hanging around

7
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,540
that Tong Sui shop for half a month

8
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:23,560
just to sneak a peek at me?

9
00:01:24,440 --> 00:01:26,720
I just liked their Tong Sui

10
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:28,200
and saw you, you know, by chance.

11
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:32,280
And who was the one

12
00:01:32,800 --> 00:01:34,400
who waited outside my place for hours

13
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:35,840
just to celebrate with me

14
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,440
after my Gaokao

15
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:39,680
and almost got mistaken for a thief?

16
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,760
How is that my fault?

17
00:01:42,760 --> 00:01:44,280
That person just had bad eyesight.

18
00:01:45,800 --> 00:01:46,640
Alright.

19
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:50,120
Then...

20
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,120
who was the one

21
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,740
who'd rather wear that awful clothes

22
00:01:54,740 --> 00:01:56,920
and take that job just to work with me?

23
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:02,800
Hey, don't tell me

24
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:06,000
you're bringing up old stuff here

25
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,720
just to stop me from sleeping in your bed.

26
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:15,240
You weren't this chubby before.

27
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,500
You think I look bad now?

28
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:19,480
No, I don't.

29
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,080
You've never been pretty.

30
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:23,920
Hey...

31
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:39,160
Kiss me.

32
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:44,880
Time to sleep.

33
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:54,880
Wai,

34
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:56,780
what's that supposed to mean?

35
00:02:58,320 --> 00:02:59,480
What do you mean?

36
00:03:01,040 --> 00:03:02,680
What's the point of doing all this?

37
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,800
After that,

38
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,440
I might be leaving Mancheng.

39
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:14,640
Maybe,

40
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,440
I'll never come back again.

41
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:20,560
Can you really let it go?

42
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:23,190
If I can't,
what difference does it make?

43
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,840
You're about to get engaged.

44
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,480
Go to sleep.

45
00:03:40,920 --> 00:03:41,800
What I'm saying is,

46
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,120
can you really let go

47
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,440
of your career and leave here?

48
00:03:58,280 --> 00:03:59,360
Chen Aming.

49
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,240
Can you tell me just one truth?

50
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,160
Just one.

51
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:06,880
Why did you really come back?

52
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,720
My name is...

53
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:10,090
Don't call me Chen Aming.

54
00:04:10,090 --> 00:04:11,000
My name is Yu Kun.

55
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,400
Yu Kun.

56
00:04:16,680 --> 00:04:17,960
Yu Kun, Yu Kun.

57
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:18,800
When will you finally

58
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:19,880
face the real you?

59
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:20,920
Then when will you

60
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,280
stop turning cold out of nowhere?

61
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:36,280
All these years, I've never changed.

62
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,600
The one who's changed is you.

63
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:46,160
A coward
who even abandoned his real name.

64
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,760
(What I left behind wasn't my name.)

65
00:04:55,760 --> 00:04:58,560
(It was my regret, my pain,)

66
00:04:58,560 --> 00:04:59,400
(and...)

67
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,560
(my weakness.)

68
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:11,680
Same as always, please.

69
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:25,240
I forgot to bring cash again.

70
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:27,960
Can you put it on Zhou Haoran's tab?

71
00:05:28,240 --> 00:05:30,680
Putting it on hiss tab means
putting it on my sister's.

72
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:33,040
Putting it on my sister's means
it's on me.

73
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:36,640
Total sister protector.

74
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,020
Don't feel like owing me?

75
00:05:40,440 --> 00:05:41,440
You can work it off.

76
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,760
Give it a shot, it's stress-relieving.

77
00:06:05,120 --> 00:06:06,200
Have you made up your mind?

78
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,200
Yeah.

79
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,640
But let me make one thing clear first.

80
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,880
You're free to go.

81
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:19,680
Are you staying to help me turn this around,

82
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,520
or are you leaving?

83
00:06:23,400 --> 00:06:24,380
The door's right there.

84
00:06:27,040 --> 00:06:28,240
If we go through with this,

85
00:06:28,240 --> 00:06:29,440
the risk is huge.

86
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:33,560
Anything we do comes with risk.

87
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:35,920
If we don't try, how will we know?

88
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:38,520
I'm with Boss on this.

89
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:04,040
Ding Daang.

90
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:06,400
Ding Daang.

91
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,220
Ding Daang.

92
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,200
Stop following me.

93
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:18,520
We finally met again.

94
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:20,960
Do you really want to waste

95
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,820
the last of our time
on wandering like this?

96
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,120
Waste?

97
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,320
Are you saying every second with me

98
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,360
is just a waste?

99
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:32,390
Who gave you the right to decide for me?

100
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,920
But Miaomiao needs to go to school.

101
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,920
What's wrong with me paying her tuition?

102
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,120
This is my family matter.

103
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,520
Not your concern.

104
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,200
But I…

105
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,920
Aren't we in the same boat?

106
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:53,840
Ding Daang.

107
00:07:55,680 --> 00:07:57,000
I owe you too much.

108
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,200
I'm sorry.

109
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:03,600
Aming…

110
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:05,540
There's no need
for apologies between us.

111
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,160
And didn't we agree

112
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:09,040
we'd face everything together?

113
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,640
I've made up my mind.

114
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,360
I'm going abroad with Professor Luo.

115
00:08:24,920 --> 00:08:26,160
What did you just say?

116
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:31,760
Aming…

117
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:33,760
You're mad at me, aren't you?

118
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:37,200
My dad's health isn't good.

119
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,080
Didn't you say…

120
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,680
you'd go back
and help him after graduation?

121
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:44,680
It's alright.

122
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,340
You could stay for two years.

123
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:47,360
After that, I'll go abroad

124
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,400
and we'll do what you love.

125
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,240
Ding Daang.

126
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,840
I don't want to waste time.

127
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:55,920
Sorry.

128
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:03,920
Not your concern.

129
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,000
It's not even a week yet.

130
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:09,560
So,

131
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:11,540
it's not for you to decide.

132
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,040
Put me down.

133
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:20,480
Will you be good?

134
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:21,720
No.

135
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,080
Let go of me.

136
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,360
The last wild fling before marriage.

137
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:37,800
That kind of thrill is just human nature.

138
00:09:37,800 --> 00:09:39,540
Or is it a sign
of disrespect for marriage?

139
00:09:39,920 --> 00:09:40,800
I mean,

140
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,520
did you bring Gu Ruomai as a streamer

141
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,040
just to get close to me?

142
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,000
Ding Daang.

143
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,840
Where have you been?

144
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,920
I want to have a talk with you.

145
00:09:51,520 --> 00:09:52,360
Ding Daang.

146
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,600
Your fiancé...

147
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,480
He's kind of interesting.

148
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,680
Cold and heartless, I see.

149
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:01,960
Have you already forgotten

150
00:10:02,880 --> 00:10:03,720
Chen

151
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:04,960
Miao

152
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:06,920
Miao?

153
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:39,220
♪I forgot this is a movie meant for one♪

154
00:10:43,620 --> 00:10:50,980
♪Somehow you're still here,
crying with me♪

155
00:10:55,430 --> 00:10:57,370
♪They say♪

156
00:10:57,780 --> 00:11:06,160
♪Lovers should never hold hands
while watching a sad movie♪

157
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:09,660
♪Some endings cannot be changed♪

158
00:11:09,880 --> 00:11:15,830
♪They don't belong in sweet memories♪

159
00:11:17,210 --> 00:11:22,970
♪I've already lost you♪

160
00:11:22,970 --> 00:11:28,450
♪Thinking of it takes my breath away♪

161
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:34,700
♪The movie ends, so many couples around♪

162
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:39,480
♪Yet none were ever like us♪

163
00:11:40,590 --> 00:11:44,620
♪The past will always pass♪

164
00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:52,530
♪If you could still hold me tight
in your arms♪

165
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:56,250
♪I'd believe
that there are miracles in love♪

166
00:11:56,810 --> 00:12:02,460
♪I'd prove
that I'm still in love with you♪

167
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:08,450
♪I've learned how to cherish
what we had♪

168
00:12:08,450 --> 00:12:14,710
♪But sadly, it's not you♪
